This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama, declaring November 11, 2013, as Veterans Day in the United States. The proclamation acknowledges and honors the service and sacrifice of all veterans who have defended the country. It emphasizes the ongoing obligations to provide respect and care to veterans, and the importance of giving them opportunities in the workforce. The proclamation also calls for remembering and supporting wounded, missing, and fallen veterans and their families. It highlights the distinguished service of veterans and encourages Americans to celebrate and honor them through public ceremonies and private prayers.